FFmpeg
------

PlayerKit links against FFmpeg (https://ffmpeg.org/), which is distributed
under the GNU Lesser General Public License v2.1 or later (LGPL v2.1+).

  - FFmpeg source:        https://ffmpeg.org/releases/ffmpeg-8.1.2.tar.gz
  - FFmpeg build script:  scripts/build_ffmpeg.sh
  - Built xcframeworks:  Sources/CFFmpeg/xcframeworks/{libavcodec,libavformat,
                          libavutil,libswresample,libswscale}.xcframework

The pre-built FFmpeg xcframeworks are committed to the refluxio/PlayerKit
independent repository. Inside the reflux monorepo they are git-ignored and
regenerated locally by `scripts/build_ffmpeg.sh`. They were built with
`--enable-gpl` disabled, so only LGPL-compatible components are included.

### LGPL compliance — replacing FFmpeg

Under LGPL v2.1, users of PlayerKit must be able to replace the FFmpeg
libraries with their own builds. To do so:

1. Build FFmpeg from source:
   ```bash
   cd PlayerKit
   scripts/build_ffmpeg.sh
   ```
   This regenerates the 5 xcframeworks under `Sources/CFFmpeg/xcframeworks/`.

2. Or supply your own pre-built xcframeworks by replacing the contents of
   `Sources/CFFmpeg/xcframeworks/` and re-linking:
   ```bash
   xcrun swift build
   ```

3. Applications that statically link PlayerKit must also provide their
   users a way to relink against a modified FFmpeg (e.g. by distributing
   the PlayerKit object files alongside the executable, or by using dynamic
   linking instead of static).


